---
/**
 * transactions-isolation · ssi-deep-dive · Figure 3 — Level 3 dangerous-structure graph.
 *
 * Copied VERBATIM from docs/transactions-isolation/ssi-deep-dive.html (the inline
 * <svg> pivot/two-rw-edge figure in §3 + its figcaption). Lives as an .astro
 * component for the same reason as Fig1/Fig2: raw inline SVG with kebab-case
 * attributes is unreliable inside MDX, but is plain HTML inside .astro.
 *
 * The source page defined the arrowhead markers once in a body-level
 * <svg width="0" height="0"> and referenced them via url(#arwA). To keep this
 * figure self-contained, the #arwA marker it uses is inlined here in its own
 * <defs>.
 */
---

<figure>
    <svg
        viewBox="0 0 520 150"
        role="img"
        aria-label="T-in points to T-pivot via an rw edge, and T-pivot points to T-out via a second rw edge; the pivot is the meeting point"
    >
        <defs>
            <marker
                id="arwA"
                viewBox="0 0 10 10"
                refX="8.5"
                refY="5"
                markerWidth="7"
                markerHeight="7"
                orient="auto-start-reverse"
            >
                <path d="M0,0 L10,5 L0,10 z" fill="#7a1f12"></path>
            </marker>
        </defs>
        <g font-family="ui-sans-serif,system-ui,sans-serif">
            <circle cx="70" cy="80" r="40" fill="#fff" stroke="#1f3a5a" stroke-width="1.5"></circle>
            <text x="70" y="78" text-anchor="middle" font-size="12" font-weight="700" fill="#1f3a5a"
                >T-in</text
            >
            <text x="70" y="93" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f">reads x</text>
            <circle cx="260" cy="80" r="46" fill="#fbfaf2" stroke="#7a1f12" stroke-width="2"
            ></circle>
            <text
                x="260"
                y="76"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="13"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#7a1f12">T-pivot</text
            >
            <text x="260" y="92" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >in + out flag</text
            >
            <circle cx="450" cy="80" r="40" fill="#fff" stroke="#2f5d3a" stroke-width="1.5"
            ></circle>
            <text
                x="450"
                y="78"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="12"
                font-weight="700"
                fill="#2f5d3a">T-out</text
            >
            <text x="450" y="93" text-anchor="middle" font-size="8.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >commits first</text
            >
            <line
                x1="112"
                y1="80"
                x2="212"
                y2="80"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"
                marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>
            <text
                x="162"
                y="68"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                fill="#7a1f12"
                font-weight="700">rw</text
            >
            <line
                x1="308"
                y1="80"
                x2="408"
                y2="80"
                stroke="#7a1f12"
                stroke-width="1.5"
                marker-end="url(#arwA)"></line>
            <text
                x="358"
                y="68"
                text-anchor="middle"
                font-size="10"
                fill="#7a1f12"
                font-weight="700">rw</text
            >
            <text x="260" y="140" text-anchor="middle" font-size="10.5" fill="#6b675f"
                >break ANY one of the three → the cycle can never close</text
            >
        </g>
    </svg>
    <figcaption>
        You don't materialise the graph or wait for the cycle to close — you spot one node that is
        the meeting point of two rw-edges.
    </figcaption>
</figure>
